article.description: St. Francis, NY 61, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 58
article.headline: St. Francis, NY 61, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 58
article.linkText: St. Francis, NY 61, Mount St. Mary's, Md. 58
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- Ricky Cadell scored 21 points and Justin Newton hit two late free throws, leading St. Francis (N.Y.) in a 61-58 win over Mount St. Mary's on Thursday night. Akeem Bennett added 11 points for the Terriers (6-9, 3-2 Northeast Conference), who shot 48.9 percent for the floor (22-for-45). The Mountaineers produced just a 34.5 mark (20-for-58). Cadell converted a three-point play to put the Terriers up 57-54 with just over 3 minutes to play. But Kelly Beidler's layup capped a 4-0 run over the course of 2 minutes to put the Mountaineers ahead. Bennett dropped in layup of his own to put St. Francis ahead 59-58 with 40 second left and Newton's foul shots sealed it. The Mountaineers missed a pair of 3s, a layup and turned the ball over in the final 25 seconds. Beidler scored 15 for the Mountaineers (4-12, 1-4).
